CBRE is pleased to present 23 Byrnes Street, Botany to the market For Sale via Public Auction, commencing 10:30am Tuesday, 8th September 2020. This vacant block of land presents an outstanding opportunity to acquire one of the last remaining land parcels in South Sydney.

The site is located within the well established and thriving industrial and business precinct of Botany, alongside neighbours such as One Drop Brewing, The Assembly Label, Jungle Brothers Strength & Movement and others.

The opportunity:
-	569sqm* vacant parcel of land
-	Cleared and levelled
-	IN1 General Industrial (SEPP) Zoning
-	Located in a popular industrial precinct
-	3km* from Sydney Airport
-	5.5km* from Port Botany
-	12km* from Sydney CBD
-	Rare, vacant land in Botany

The property will be sold via Public Auction, commencing 10:30am, Tuesday 8th September 2020 at Auction Works, Mezzanine Level, 50 Margaret Street, Sydney.

To arrange a site visit, Information Memorandum or contract, please contact the exclusive CBRE selling agents.

CBRE as the exclusive selling agents, is pleased to present 1637-1647 Botany Road, Botany.

The site is DA Approved for a mixed use development, consisting of 36 residential apartments and 5 commercial/retail suites above basement parking. The development is approved for a total GFA of 3,632sqm* and NSA of 3,055.6sqm*, along with 97 basement car spaces. The approval provides an opportunity for incoming investors, downsizers and families to invest or reside in a very desirable suburb within a rapidly growing area. 1637-1647 Botany Road is well positioned, with easy access to public transport and is just moments from Sydney Kingsford Smith Airport. 


1637-1647 Botany Road benefits from the following key highlights:

- DA Approval for 36 apartments and 5 commercial/retail suites 
- 97 secure basement car spaces 
- Large 1,816sqm* site area
- Approved GFA of 3,632sqm* and NSA of 3,055.6sqm*
- Close proximity to Sydney Kingsford Smith Airport and frequent bus services along Botany Road
- Opportunity for investors, downsizers and families to invest or reside in a very desirable location
- B1 Neighbourhood Centre zoning, FSR 2:1 and 14m height limit

1637-1647 Botany Road will be offered for sale via Expression of Interest closing Tuesday, 1 June 2021 at 4:00pm.
